Indoor navigation project for visually impaired person using DEAD REACKONING technique and periodic
recalibration suing already installed wifi access points .

This project makes use of the accelerometer readings to detect when the step is taken and the uses 
magnetometer reading to detect the heading of the user.

The project map was designed based on Computer Science department Indian institute of Technology,Guwahati 
ground floor map and we use voice commands to give direction to the user.


How to use:
1.Enter your height in cm
2.Select the starting location
3.select the destination landmark
4.press the start button while keeping your mobile phone in one hand and in a horizontal position and take ypur steps normally trying to keep the phone horizontal.

